Thank you, Xavier.

00:18:07.510 --> 00:18:09.870
I never like to
follow his remarks.

00:18:09.870 --> 00:18:11.440
But anyway, here I am.

00:18:11.440 --> 00:18:14.450
I also want to just thank
Jonathan for having us

00:18:14.450 --> 00:18:19.560
here at Google and
mention, as Xavier said, we

00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:24.770
rely on Google daily, hourly.

00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:29.740
At our office, we actually
have all of our shared

00:18:29.740 --> 00:18:32.450
files in Google Drive.

00:18:32.450 --> 00:18:35.460
And that's what we go
to, we really rely on.

00:18:35.460 --> 00:18:38.220
And I know it's donated to us.

00:18:38.220 --> 00:18:40.280
And we're incredibly grateful.

00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:45.960
We also being based in DC, the
way that we communicate weekly

00:18:45.960 --> 00:18:49.190
for our staff meeting with
our colleague in Chicago,

00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:52.170
with Xavier, is via
Google Hangouts.

00:18:52.170 --> 00:18:55.390
So we're really
grateful to what you all

00:18:55.390 --> 00:18:57.760
have been able to create
that makes our work possible

00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:00.610
and makes it possible
for us to stay

00:19:00.610 --> 00:19:02.660
in constant communication
with one another

00:19:02.660 --> 00:19:04.960
to strengthen our efforts.

00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.940
So as I mentioned,
the campaign is

00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:09.610
involved in a lot of
different strategies

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:11.190
to end life without
parole for kids.

00:19:11.190 --> 00:19:14.780
We do advocacy, litigation,
public education,

00:19:14.780 --> 00:19:16.440
and coalition building.

00:19:16.440 --> 00:19:18.930
We host an annual
convening in DC every year,

00:19:18.930 --> 00:19:20.500
which we would
welcome you all to.

00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:24.070
It's a great opportunity
to learn about not

00:19:24.070 --> 00:19:27.500
only the issues and the
challenges people are facing

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:30.430
and where you learn best
practices from one another,

00:19:30.430 --> 00:19:32.873
but to learn from the
people directly impacted

00:19:32.873 --> 00:19:37.100
and to be in a room with them
to better understand their life

00:19:37.100 --> 00:19:39.770
experiences, like Xavier's
and other ICAN members,

00:19:39.770 --> 00:19:42.060
as well as victim
family members.

00:19:42.060 --> 00:19:44.160
Often times, people
are surprised to know

00:19:44.160 --> 00:19:46.950
that we work with people
who've lost loved ones to youth

00:19:46.950 --> 00:19:48.240
violence.

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:51.630
But the reality is
that not all of them

00:19:51.630 --> 00:19:56.850
want to see the system
throw these kids away.

00:19:56.850 --> 00:20:00.290
Many of them find it healing
to see the people who

00:20:00.290 --> 00:20:04.047
killed their loved ones out and
doing well in the community.

00:20:04.047 --> 00:20:05.880
These are some of the
most courageous people

00:20:05.880 --> 00:20:06.880
I've ever met.

00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:09.380
And they inspire us
in our work every day.

00:20:09.380 --> 00:20:12.080
And we're actually
in the year ahead

00:20:12.080 --> 00:20:15.886
aspiring to launch a national
network similar to ICAN

00:20:15.886 --> 00:20:17.830
of victim family
members to make sure

00:20:17.830 --> 00:20:20.990
that their voices are heard
because too often, it's only

00:20:20.990 --> 00:20:25.660
the victims that are seeking
punitive policies and sentences

00:20:25.660 --> 00:20:26.740
that we hear from.

00:20:26.740 --> 00:20:29.770
And so in the year
ahead, we are looking

00:20:29.770 --> 00:20:31.640
to better connect
with those folks

00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:34.020
and create a national network.

00:20:34.020 --> 00:20:37.660
So we welcome the
brilliance of Googlers

00:20:37.660 --> 00:20:39.990
in figuring out how to
stay better connected

00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:43.640
and using technology to do that.

00:20:43.640 --> 00:20:49.910
We hope that more than anything
that you'll share information

00:20:49.910 --> 00:20:53.450
about this practice, you'll
share Xavier's story.

00:20:53.450 --> 00:20:57.090
We have a video that features
a number of the ICAN members

00:20:57.090 --> 00:20:59.620
who worked in Nevada
last year and helped

00:20:59.620 --> 00:21:02.900
to pass a bill
unanimously to ban life

00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:05.030
without parole for children.

00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:07.507
We think that the
more people recognize

00:21:07.507 --> 00:21:09.590
that this is something our
country and our country

00:21:09.590 --> 00:21:13.510
alone does to our kids, and
people who have kids or know

00:21:13.510 --> 00:21:16.697
teenagers or were
once teenagers,

00:21:16.697 --> 00:21:18.280
when you start to
think about the fact

00:21:18.280 --> 00:21:25.690
that kids are-- especially kids
who grow up in environments

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:29.610
that are oppressive
and do not provide

00:21:29.610 --> 00:21:31.860
the kind of opportunities
that many of us

00:21:31.860 --> 00:21:36.570
have had-- that the
circumstances really shape

00:21:36.570 --> 00:21:40.650
young people and that when
they're given opportunity,

00:21:40.650 --> 00:21:42.150
they can change and
do great things.

00:21:42.150 --> 00:21:45.200
And so I think when
people recognize that

00:21:45.200 --> 00:21:47.450
and they know that this is
something that we're doing,

00:21:47.450 --> 00:21:49.420
people want to get
engaged and involved.

00:21:49.420 --> 00:21:54.235
And so we'd welcome your
participation joining us.

00:21:54.235 --> 00:21:57.940
If you go to our website, you
can sign up for our newsletters

00:21:57.940 --> 00:21:59.910
and stay involved
and stay posted

00:21:59.910 --> 00:22:03.020
on the various developments
around the country.

00:22:03.020 --> 00:22:04.520
And if you go to
our website, you'll

00:22:04.520 --> 00:22:09.040
see that we would also welcome
volunteers to help us even

00:22:09.040 --> 00:22:11.110
improve our website.

00:22:11.110 --> 00:22:15.700
We certainly look to the
pros for that sort of thing.

00:22:15.700 --> 00:22:21.270
I always tell people if your
kid gets locked up, call me.

00:22:21.270 --> 00:22:23.190
And I'll look to
you for whatever

00:22:23.190 --> 00:22:24.640
it is that you guys do best.

00:22:24.640 --> 00:22:28.030
And I know at Google, you guys
come with incredible ideas

00:22:28.030 --> 00:22:29.010
and technology.

00:22:29.010 --> 00:22:33.780
And that's something that
we would value in partnering

00:22:33.780 --> 00:22:35.090
with you guys in the future.

00:22:35.090 --> 00:22:39.420
So the other thing that
we think that is really

00:22:39.420 --> 00:22:41.940
remarkable about the young
people that we work with--

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:43.910
and many of them
not young anymore,

00:22:43.910 --> 00:22:46.740
but who are in the
inside-- is that they

00:22:46.740 --> 00:22:50.570
have an incredible ability
to not only, like Xavier

00:22:50.570 --> 00:22:53.180
was saying, reflect on
sort of what their life

00:22:53.180 --> 00:22:57.130
experiences have been and how
they've overcome the traumas

00:22:57.130 --> 00:23:00.980
and helped to really
rehabilitate themselves,

00:23:00.980 --> 00:23:02.960
many of them have
incredible skills.

00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:05.167
Many of them are
artists we know.

00:23:05.167 --> 00:23:06.875
We get some of the
most brilliant artwork

00:23:06.875 --> 00:23:08.610
sent to our office.

00:23:08.610 --> 00:23:11.520
And so one idea we
had was wouldn't it

00:23:11.520 --> 00:23:15.030
be great to have a Google
Doodle from a juvenile lifer

00:23:15.030 --> 00:23:19.209
to demonstrate that this is the
potential of these young people

00:23:19.209 --> 00:23:21.250
that we've told are worth
nothing more than dying

00:23:21.250 --> 00:23:24.360
in prison and to
people recognize

00:23:24.360 --> 00:23:26.700
that this is a
population that continues

00:23:26.700 --> 00:23:29.900
to live despite being
told that and continues

00:23:29.900 --> 00:23:32.150
to hope for a second chance?

00:23:32.150 --> 00:23:33.950
So those are a couple of things.

00:23:33.950 --> 00:23:38.080
We welcome your
ideas, as I said.

00:23:38.080 --> 00:23:42.220
I am just excited to be
here and for the opportunity

00:23:42.220 --> 00:23:46.325
and to tap into the world
of ideas that you all bring.

00:23:46.325 --> 00:23:48.480
So thank you again, Jonathan.

00:23:48.480 --> 00:23:53.780
